<arggraph id="micro_c187" topic_id="video_games_bad_for_families" stance="con">
  <edu id="e1"><![CDATA[Video games do not have a negative impact on family life.]]></edu>
  <edu id="e2"><![CDATA[This is a classic example of treating a symptom and ignoring the disease.]]></edu>
  <edu id="e3"><![CDATA[Would you say does tending a garden negatively affect family life? Of course you wouldn't.]]></edu>
  <edu id="e4"><![CDATA[Both are activities designed to relax a person.]]></edu>
  <edu id="e5"><![CDATA[Such activities cannot be inherently bad.]]></edu>
  <edu id="e6"><![CDATA[It's what the person does with that activity that makes it bad.]]></edu>
